notesStmt.note: Dimensions of original manuscript: 352 x 240 (222 x 137) mm bound to 160 x 100 mm.
Laid, non-European paper; no visible chain lines

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Collection of Jāmī's poems and prose writings. A table of contents has been written in (f. 1r) and some titles have been added by a later hand in black ink on the gold cartouches in the headpieces before each new work.

supportDesc.foliation: Modern pagination added in pencil, upper outer corners; catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 25 long lines or 25 lines in four columns.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Dual-page illuminated first opening in blue, black, red and gold with blue finials reaching into the margins (p. 2-3); illuminated headpieces in gold, blue, red and green before each new work (p. 88, 124, 148, 174, 212, 276, 360, 440, 490, 528, 702, 716, 804, 868, 924, 976, 1006, 1021, 1036, 1051, 1056). Rubrications in red; textblock border ruled in gold, light green, gold and blue with gold rules between columns.

binding.p: Bound in black leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II) with inlaid, gold-stamped central mandorla, two pendants on the vertical axis and cornerpieces. Inside covers have red leather doublure with gold filigree central mandorla and cornerpieces, each set over a polychrome (black, orange, blue, light green) background; matching filigree design on the inside of the flap. Endbands in blue and peach.

origin.p: Portions of the copy completed at different times and not all sections are dated: one section completed in Shaʻbān 984 (p. 865) and another section completed at the end of Rajab 984 (p. 1072). One colophon says the copy was made by Aḥmad Jāmī (p. 973).
